From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 15:35:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Keep DualSense mono logical endpoint on disconnect.

The Pulse device backing a DualSense/Edge mono speaker is still removed on
physical unplug. However, Spider-Man Remastered can keep app-side state tied to
the MMDevice endpoint and then fail to follow the replacement endpoint after a
controller model switch.

With winepulse exposing the DualSense mono speaker through a stable app-facing
endpoint id, keep that logical MMDevice in the active list as NOTPRESENT instead
of deleting it and sending OnDeviceRemoved. When the next physical DualSense
speaker sink appears, MMDevice_Create() reactivates the same GUID and sends the
normal add notification, while the old physical Pulse sink remains fully gone.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 20 ++------------------
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 18 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index 33333333333..44444444444 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -1588,30 +1588,14 @@ static DWORD WINAPI update_thread_proc(void *user)
                     EnterCriticalSection(&g_notif_lock);
                     LIST_FOR_EACH_ENTRY(wrapper, &g_notif_clients, struct NotificationClientWrapper, entry)
                     {
                         IMMNotificationClient_OnDeviceStateChanged(wrapper->client, devid, dev->state);
-                        if (dualsense_mono_endpoint)
-                            IMMNotificationClient_OnDeviceRemoved(wrapper->client, devid);
                     }
                     LeaveCriticalSection(&g_notif_lock);
 
                     if (dualsense_mono_endpoint)
-                    {
-                        LONG delete_ret;
-
-                        TRACE("Removing disconnected DualSense mono endpoint %s from active device list.\n",
-                                debugstr_guid(&dev->devguid));
-                        if ((delete_ret = RegDeleteTreeW(root, guidstr)) && delete_ret != ERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND)
-                            WARN("Failed to remove disconnected DualSense mono endpoint registry key %s: %lu\n",
-                                    debugstr_guid(&dev->devguid), delete_ret);
-                        dev->removed = TRUE;
-                        if (MMDevice_def_play == dev)
-                            MMDevice_def_play = NULL;
-                        list_remove(&dev->entry);
-                        list_init(&dev->entry);
-                        if (!dev->ref)
-                            MMDevice_Destroy(dev);
-                    }
+                        TRACE("Keeping disconnected DualSense mono endpoint %s for stable app-facing hotplug.\n",
+                                debugstr_guid(&dev->devguid));
 
                     break;
                 }
             }
